The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Anil buys 50% of UK games firm
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Anil buys 50% of UK games firm
          OUR BUREAU                              
	Mumbai, April 5: Reliance Big Entertainment (RBEL), an Anil Ambani group company, will acquire a 50 per cent shareholding in UK-based Codemasters, a developer and publisher of video games.        
	This investment in Codemasters is alongside existing investor Balderton Capital, a European venture capital firm that first invested in Codemasters in 2005.        
	RBELs gaming division, Zapak Digital Entertainment which is the countrys largest gaming firm, will oversee the investment in Codemasters, said a company release.        
	Codemasters, a gaming company with revenues of $150 million, has franchises in cricket games (The Ashes), racing games (Formula 1, Dirt2 and Race Driver Grid), performance games (Dance Factory) and military simulations (Operation Flashpoint 2).        
	Rohit Sharma, CEO of Zapak, said: We are excited to partner with Codemasters and believe its very strong technology, development and distribution presence will complement our global gaming portfolio. Zapaks global strength in mobile gaming will enhance Codemasters ability to fully leverage its attractive franchises such as its racing and cricket games.                                                                                                                                       
